The total width of an element is calculated as follows:

Total width = width + padding-left + padding-right + border-left-width + border-right-width + margin-left + margin-right
Similarly, the total height is calculated using the same formula with height, padding-top, padding-bottom, border-top-width, border-bottom-width, margin-top, and margin-bottom.

Example HTML and CSS
HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>CSS Box Model Example</title>
  <style>
    .box {
      width: 200px;
      height: 100px;
      border: 2px solid black;
      padding: 10px;
      margin: 20px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="box">This is a box</div>
</body>
</html>
Use code with caution.

