Explanation
The .box class styles the div element with a width, height, border, padding, and margin.
The width and height properties set the dimensions of the content area.
The border property adds a border around the content and padding.
The padding property creates space between the content and the border.
The margin property creates space between the border and other elements.
By understanding the box model and its components, you can effectively control the layout and spacing of elements on your web pages.
